                    <msContents>
                        <summary>
                            <p>ترجمه پندنامه عطار</p>
                            <p>A metrical Turkish translation of the Pand-náma of Faridu'd-Din 'Attár by
                                Amrí of Adrianople (d. 988/1580). See Flügel, Vienna Catalogue, vol. III, p. 415,
                                where another copy of the work is described, and Rieu, B.M.T.C., pp. 154 and 261.
                                Begins (f. 2):</p>
                            <p>مبدع كونين سلطان قديم ابتدا کردم بنام آن كريم</p>
                            <p>The translation, written in the same metre as the original poem and dedicated
                                to Prince Báyazid, a son of Sultán Sulaymán I (see Gibb, Hist. of Ottoman Poetry,
                                vol. 1, pp. 10-11), begins on f. 4:</p>
                            <p>نور ایمان ویردی خاک آدمه حمد بی حد اول خدای عالمه</p>
                            <p>and is followed by miscellaneous Turkish and Arabic verses (ff. 37b-40b).</p>
                            <p>Ff. 43 of 19.8 x 13.6 cm and 15 ll. Clear naskh, pointed, with rubrications.
                                Transcribed by Darwísh Safar and completed in 1035/1625-6. This MS. was
                                presented to Professor Browne in April, 1908, by Dr Riza Tevfiq.</p>
                        </summary>
                        <msItem xml:id="W_9-item1">
                            <author key="person_107148977" cert="medium">
                                <persName xml:lang="en">Emrî of Adrianople, d.
                                    988/1580</persName>
